lder phase test gate instead of the accepted `final-coverage` test gate\n- I narrowed those rows to focused profile endpoints like:\n  - `profile_page.cj::renderProfileRoute`\n  - `profile_page.cj::buildProfileTopBar`\n  - `profile_route_service.cj::buildLogoutTransition`\n  - `profile_route_service.cj::resetAfterLogout`\n  - `profile_store.cj::logout`\n\n**High-risk gaps fixed**\n- Replaced lingering broad-shell verification references in the profile cluster with precise feature-level endpoints.\n- Aligned profile verification evidence with the accepted final test gate.\n- Made the intentional placeholder behavior explicit and shared in code instead of repeating raw literals.\n\n**Remaining deferred gaps**\n- None added.\n- I did not mark any new deferred items.\n- The broader whole-project medium findings about overall endpoint/UI concentration in `bootstrap_page.cj` and `home_page.cj` remain outside this requested cluster sweep.\n\n**Tests**\n- No new tests added.\n- Existing focused profile tests remain the evidence source:\n  - `entry/src/test/cangjie/phase06_profile_capabilities_verification_test.cj`\n- Verified the accepted test command still passes after the code cleanup.\n\n**Commands run**\n- `python D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\source_coverage\\patch_authority.py --help`\n- `python D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\source_coverage\\patch_authority.py --kind matrix --authority D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.json --patch <temp patch> --markdown D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.md --plan-json D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\plan.json --target-project D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n- `cjpm test --target aarch64-linux-ohos` from `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie` with the env overlay from `translation-inputs/test-build-reports/final-coverage/test-build-report.md`\n\n**Build result**\n- PASS\n- Manual reproduction of the final accepted test gate succeeded:\n  -